      • playFetch

        public java.lang.String playFetch(Dog dog)
        For this method, our child will take an instance of a dog to play fetch with. The age of the dog will determine the resulting string as follows: If the dog is younger than 2 or older than 12, return "didn't fetch the ball" If the dog is 2-5 (inclusive), return "got the ball but didn't bring it back" For any other age, return "fetched the ball"
        Parameters:
        dog -
        Returns:
        string with appropriate phrase
